He said Lamb made the fatal emergency call sometime afterwards.
By the end of the day, there was another death: Lamb took his own life when the police killed him.
A day after the shooting at the university, which forced students and faculty to hide behind closed doors, authorities are still trying to get a picture of what motivated Lamb.
The details released by investigators at both ends of the state, as well as what students and staff who knew him said, helped draw a picture of a talented but potentially difficult teacher.
Students said they were looking forward to his lessons.
Police in Gautier, where Prentiss died, said he had no history of violence or a criminal history.
Schmidt himself had mentioned Lamb in a book he wrote, in which he mentioned the "wonderful people" with whom he shared his academic life.
Both taught in the Department of Social Sciences and History, whose faculty consists of 17 members, and many students attended classes from both.
At the same time, there were some tendencies to problematic behaviors.
